text.tspan: I look away to Thee, my Lord
Experience of Christ — As Food and Drink
And daily I may come to Thee—
And drink of the Fountain of life!
God in the Son as Spirit flows—
The Triune God, my sure supply!
We in one Body were baptized;
The Spirit we now can all drink!
We drink and His riches receive!
We come! We come! We come to drink of Thee!
We come to taste Thy living streams,
We come to be filled with Thy grace!
We sing and drink the whole day long;
We’re filled as we speak forth Thy Word—
Yes, filled in spirit as we sing
With grace in our hearts to the Lord!
O hear the cry that’s going forth—
O join this cry; call sinners far
To drink of this Eternal One!
Do come! Do come! O come to drink of Him!
Yes, come and taste His living streams,
O come and be filled with His grace!
